body: "## Source\nGitHub issue #490 (version 2026.7.9).\n\n## Reproduction\n```bash\npm log some-id \"a note\"\n# Error: Unknown command log\n# Next steps: Did you mean: extension catalog, package catalog?\n```\n\n## Problem\nThe suggester ranks by substring containment (\"log\" ⊂ \"cataLOG\"), so both catalog subcommands outrank the commands an agent actually means — `history`, `comments`, `notes`. An agent following the hint is misdirected to the extension catalog instead of the item-history surface.\n\n## Proposed ranking\n1. Alias/synonym table for the top verbs agents guess (log→history/comments/notes, ls→list, rm→delete, …)\n2. Edit distance on the command token\n3. Substring hits last\n\nEven a small hardcoded synonym table removes most misdirection. The rest of the unknown-command error contract (structured JSON, recovery bundle, exit 2) is good — only the ranking misleads.\n\n## Why it matters for agents\nStateless agents guess verbs constantly; suggestion quality determines whether recovery costs one retry or a full `pm --help` roundtrip (96 lines) plus re-orientation. Related: pm-gdi7 covers the unknown-OPTION flag-suggestion gap; this covers unknown-COMMAND ranking."
